description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MSK Rotational Physiotherapist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent, 37.5 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for motivated and experienced MSK physiotherapists to join our MSK outpatient team who are keen to specialise in MSK and to develop their specialist MSK assessment and treatment skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We deliver MSK services within both the hospital and community setting with rotations being offered in community GP practices, hydrotherapy, specialist weight management and the newly added split rotation within the prosthetic &amp; wheelchair service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an organisation we are committed to providing high quality patient care and so the successful post-holders will be welcomed into a supportive environment with a clear supervision structure through which personal and professional development is encouraged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have significant postgraduate MSK experience with a broad range of physiotherapy experience in all core areas. You must possess good communication, time-management and interpersonal skills, and be motivated and able to work efficiently both alone and as part of a team and be willing to work flexibly to meet service demands, this includes delivering a 7 day service where required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to travel between sites is an essential requirement of this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NamePaul WestEmail addresspaul.west@liverpoolft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
